==Latin==

===Noun===
'''episcopus''', '''episcopi''', ''m''; second declension noun

# [[bishop]]; an official in a Christian church who governs a region of the church sometimes called a [[diocese]], or a similar official in other religions.  An overseer or supervisor.

====Etymology====
From Greek '''[[episkopos]]''', from '''[[epi-]]''', ''upon'' or ''over'' + '''[[skopos]]''', '''sight'''.

